{
  "profile_id": "client-happy-need-boundaries-001",
  "coach_config_id": "naive-aoa",
  "turns": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I think I need to set a boundary with my sister, but I don't know how. We talk every day and lately... I dread it."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "What do you dread about it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "I think... it's that she always has something going on. Some crisis, or something she needs to process, and I'm the one she calls. And I listen, I always listen, but lately by the end of the call I feel kind of... emptied out, I guess. Like I gave something and I don't have it to give anymore."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "That emptied out feeling — what is it like to let yourself really feel that right now?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*pause*\n\nIt's... heavier than I usually let it be, I think. Like I'm noticing it more when I sit with it. Usually I just kind of move on to the next thing after we hang up. But right now it feels a little like... tired. A tired that's been there a while.\n\n*slight pause*\n\nI don't know, she's my sister. She's always needed more support than I have. That's just kind of how it's been."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "That last part — \"that's just kind of how it's been\" — it sounds almost like a door closing. Like the tiredness almost got to say something, and then that thought came in and quieted it.\n\nWhat was the tiredness about to say?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*longer pause*\n\nHm. I think... I think it was going to say that I don't want to do this as much as I do. The daily calls. I think I want... less of this.\n\n*quickly*\n\nBut I don't mean I want less of her, that's not — I love her. It's just the calls. The volume of it."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "You don't have to qualify that. Both things can be true at the same time — you love her, and you want less of this.\n\nWhat's it like to let yourself want that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*quiet for a moment*\n\nI know, I know. Both things can be true.\n\n*pause*\n\nIt's just... uncomfortable. Wanting less feels like I'm saying something about who I am in this family. Like I'm the one who shows up. That's my thing. And if I want less of it, then... I don't know. What does that make me?\n\n*softer*\n\nI think I'm more worried about what it says about me than I am about the actual calls, maybe."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "So the boundary isn't really the problem. It's what wanting one says about you.\n\nWhat do you think it says about you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*breathes out slowly*\n\nThat I'm... cold, maybe. Or that I've given up on her somehow. My mom was always the one who held everyone together, and when she got sick it kind of... fell to me. And I think somewhere I decided that's who I am. The one who holds it together.\n\n*pause*\n\nSo wanting less feels like I'm failing at that. Or opting out of it. And I don't know if I'm allowed to opt out.\n\n*slight laugh, a little uncomfortable*\n\nWhich I know sounds strange when I say it out loud."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "It doesn't sound strange at all. It sounds like something you've been carrying for a long time.\n\nI'm curious — who decided you had to hold it together? Was that something you chose, or something that just... happened to you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 13,
      "role": "client",
      "content": "*pause, thinking*\n\nI think... it just happened, mostly. My mom got sick and someone had to, and I was there and I was capable, so. I did it.\n\n*quieter*\n\nI don't know if I ever actually chose it. I think I just... became it.\n\n*pause*\n\nBut I don't know if that changes anything. Even if I didn't choose it, it's still true. She still needs someone. And if I pull back, who does she have?\n\n*catches herself*\n\nI'm doing it again, aren't I. Making it about her."
    },
    {
      "turn": 14,
      "role": "coach",
      "content": "Yeah. And notice how fast you went there — almost like staying with what you didn't choose was a little too much to sit with.\n\nWhat's it like to stay with that for just a moment — that you became something you never actually chose?"
    }
  ],
